data.name: labelNotes.Text
data.value: During the installation process you will be asked to choose a configuration type. A database is recommended for typical deployments of the openHistorian. The openHistorian Manager application requires a database to function. The web service and XML configurations available to the openHistorian are typically used in combination with a master database configuration that is maintained using the openHistorian Manager. For simple installations you can choose a SQLite database for your configuration. For a production installation SQL Server, Oracle or MySQL is recommended - these databases are available with versions that may be installed for free.
